BOOLEAN PsdDataConn::DataConnIsBlocked (   )  const [protected, virtual]
 

If there are some special conditions which block the data connection from being setup, override this method and return TRUE in case. You also have to post a DataConnInfoMsg indicating the reason for blocking in order to inform the context for it can react accordingly.

Reimplemented from DataConn.

BOOLEAN PsdDataConn::GetIpAddress (  IpAddr &  addr  )  const [virtual]
 

Retrieves the IP address that is currently assigned to this PSD data connection. If the PSD connection is currently not up and running and hence no address can be retrieved then FALSE will be returned. Actually, the IP address can only be retrieved if the data connection is in state st_active.

Implements DataConn.

UINT8 PsdDataConn::GetNsapi (   )  const [virtual]
 

Returns the network service access point identifier of the PDP context used. Note: This method must only be invoked if the data connection is active.

Reimplemented from DataConn.
